Summary: 2 topics + 5 singletons from 10 CUIs

Why the 3 medications didn't form a topic:
They DO share an ancestor: "Respiratory drug" (IC=4.8)
But IC=4.8 < floor (10.5) → rejected

Their next shared ancestor: "Drug" (IC=1.5) → even worse

Without the IC floor, "Respiratory drug" would be a topic.
But IC=4.8 means it covers ~8% of UMLS — too broad.
It would also pull in antibiotics, antihistamines, etc. from other notes.

The medications stay as singletons. Each gets its own centroid.
At query time they can still match individually.

What each topic gets:
Topic A:
  label:     "Persistent asthma" (SNOMED preferred term)
  topic_cui: C0581122 (the CUI for "Persistent asthma")
  members:   [C0264408, C2887456, C4040110]
  centroid:  mean(embeddings of 3 members), L2-normalized, 3072-dim
  subtopics: none (all 3 directly under one convergence point)

Topic B:
  label:     "Respiratory symptom"
  topic_cui: C0037090
  members:   [C0239580, C0013404]
  centroid:  mean(embeddings of 2 members), L2-normalized

Each singleton:
  label:     its own SNOMED preferred term
  topic_cui: itself
  members:   [itself]
  centroid:  its own embedding
